 <br>
However, just because I don't roleplay much, and my guild is not a RP guild, doesn't mean I don't have respect for the people that do. At all times since I started here I have always been aware that this is a roleplay preferred server and respect it as such, and respect the roleplay community.<br>
<br>
When someone roleplays with me, sometimes I roleplay back a bit, but I always speak in complete sentences and never use &quot;lol&quot; abbreviations, et al, when I'm in range of other people's earshot, so to speak.<br>
<br>
Basically, if I'm not in guildchat or private conversations, I don't say anything where others can hear me ooc. Who am I to ruin someone's experience? Is my fun more important? No. Being a part of the community and thinking of your fellow players is more important. I do enjoy seeing other's roleplay, I've seen some great encounters, and I think those that ignore it or disdain it are really missing out.<br>
<br>
I came to this server because I was brand new to the game and had no clue what all those different servers meant, and roleplay preferred sounded interesting. But I didn't come here for just roleplay, nor loot, nor tlc or no drop, or low population or anything, was just a fluke choice. As for the reason I've stayed, well:<br>
<br>
Ever wonder why so many non-roleplayers love this server? Alot of it is because the roleplayers have created an atmosphere here you can't find anywhere else.<br>
It's a bit two-faced when people come here saying there is no other server like it, then give disdain to the people (the roleplayers) that helped shape the very things you find so wonderful.<br>
<br>
There are tons of us on this server who are not roleplayers, yet we have great experiences, great friends and are heartily welcomed.  I have never found that the roleplayers see a non-roleplayer on this server and start getting the plank ready for no other reason. <br>
<br>
This guy is getting flamed, not because he doesn't roleplay but because he comes to our boards, and his first sentence in his first post is &quot;I dont give a #### about roleplay&quot;. Hell, even I found it obnoxious as hell. It's disrespectful. <p>Laraly Muddlefoot<br>
